<lb/>personal beauty so unlike the Italian
<lb/><metamark place="above" function="folio" rend="no-caret _HMp" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z007">71</metamark> stamp, their clear ruddy complexion
<lb/> and <metamark place="inline" function="caret" rend="caret _ink1" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z008">^</metamark><add place="above" rend="caret _ink1" hand="#HM" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z009">curled</add> flaxen <metamark place="inline" function="caret" rend="caret _ink1" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z010">^</metamark><add place="above" rend="caret _ink1" hand="#HM" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z011">locks</add> <del rend="single-stroke _ink1" hand="#HM" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z012">hair</del>, exclaimed, "Angles"
<lb/><del rend="single-stroke _ink1" hand="#HM" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z013">do you call them</del> (meaning <hi rend="underline">English</hi> <del rend="multi-stroke _ink1" hand="#HM" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z014">its</del> <lb/>the <metamark place="inline" function="caret" rend="caret _HMp" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z016">^</metamark><add place="above" rend="caret _HMp" hand="#HM" change="StFa" facs="#img_709_z015">modern</add> derivative) "Angles do you call
